Install Python 3
----------------

macOS:
Download and install Python 3.8.6 from https://www.python.org/downloads/mac-osx/
Launch "Update Shell Profile.command"

Windows:
Download and install Python 3.8.6 (executable installer) from https://www.python.org/downloads/windows/
Select "Add Python 3.8 to PATH" during installation.

Ubuntu:
Download and install Python 3.8.6 (XZ compressed source tarball) from https://www.python.org/downloads/source/
Extract the archive.
Open a terminal:
$ sudo apt install build-essential libffi-dev zlib1g-dev
$ cd Python-3.8.6/
$ ./configure
$ make
$ sudo make altinstall # run Python 3.8.6 side-by-side with preinstalled version

Run the Script
--------------

macOS: $ python3 Ten-Year_Minimum_Errors.py 
Windows: > python .\Ten-Year_Minimum_Errors.py
Ubuntu: $ /usr/local/bin/python3.8 Ten-Year_Minimum_Errors.py